<br>
I wondered what it was like on other servers, so I talked to some of the fellas in Celestial Tomb on Veeshan.  They  tell me that they don't do rotations.  When they go into ToV, the guild who HAS the firepower, and gets to the mob first and is fighting it first, gets the mob.  If say..  Fires of Heaven was fighting in ToV and they got wiped out, another guild might possibly walk right past them during their CR and start setting up.  <br>
<br>
There's probably blood vessle about to pop on someone's neck because I said that, so before anyone explodes into flame, please note: <br>
<br>
I'm not saying it's right, but what I'm saying is that Verant mustn't think it's so bad, since that's the way it is on most all the other servers and I haven't heard of any server splits happening in the not too distant future.<br>
<br>
The only solution is to suck it up and work with each other the best way we can, or face the alternative.<br>
